    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix double-free in nfapi_p5 unpack functions\n\n### Summary\nThere is a double free where the same memory allocation is freed twice downstream of function unpack_param_response in /repo/nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p5.c. The issue occurs when unpacking messages that contain vendor extensions, where memory is allocated during unpacking but not properly tracked, leading to attempts to free the same memory multiple times.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p5.c`: Added memset() calls to initialize message structures to zero before unpacking in all unpack functions that use unpack_tlv_list or unpack_nr_tlv_list. This ensures pointers start in a known state (NULL), preventing double-free issues when structures are later cleaned up.\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue can be reproduced by running OAI5G with NFAPI interface enabled and processing multiple parameter response messages with vendor extensions. The double-free will manifest as a crash or memory corruption during message processing.\n\n"
}